All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Closable
A Closeable represents an object holding resources to be released or closed.
Collector
An operator object responsible for retrieving shell command output files from all nodes and return a DataFrame.
CollectorSupport
Factory object responsible for creating Collector operators.
DataSource
The main interface responsible for representing an accessible data source in SeqsLab.
Executor
An operator object responsible for preprocessing (localizing) input dataframe as managed table for Spark SQL command or saving to local files for shell command execution; and it is also responsible for evaluating and updating command expression placeholders.
ExecutorSupport
Factory object responsible for creating Executor operators.
Formatter
An operator object responsible for formatting input dataframes, such as converting schema, adding or deleting columns, and encoding domain specific object.
FormatterSupport
Factory object responsible for creating Formatter operators.
Loader
An operator object responsible for loading (reading) an in-memory DataFrame or copying to local host file system from a specific data source, e.g.
LoaderSupport
Factory object responsible for creating Loader operators.
Operator
An operator that processes Spark Dataset of Row and produces a new Dataset of row.
OperatorContext
An object used in pipeline operations to represent a persistent set of properties, inputs, and outputs.
OperatorPipelineV3
The base contract interface for SeqsLab operator pipeline v3.
Partitioner
An operator object responsible for repartitioning an in-memory dataframe loaded by operator Loader to optimize downstream data processing pipeline.
PartitionerSupport
Factory object responsible for creating Partitioner operators.
Pipeline
An interface represents a complete configuration of workflow task including input parameters, dataset connection, as well as localization, computation, and delocalization workload processes.
PipelineTask
An interface represents the localization, computation, and delocalization workload processes in a pipeline task of a given variable identified by FQN (Fully Qualified Name).
PiperContext
An object used in all operations of a workflow task execution.
PiperPlugin
A plugin that can be dynamically loaded into a SeqsLab piper application.
PiperValue
An interface represents value of primitive types, e.g.
PiperValue.Type
Concrete types of all supported workflow parameters
PluginContext
An object returned when initializing this SeqsLab piper.
SupportsAggregation
The collector operator implementing this feature supports computing aggregates and returns the aggregated results as a DataFrame.
SupportsCopyToLocal
The loader operator implementing this feature supports copying storage files or directories directly to local file system.
SupportsFileLocalization
The executor operator implementing this feature supports saving input dataframe to local file system for shell command execution.
SupportsHadoopDFS
The loader operator implementing this feature indicates it supports reading or copying files and directories from storages compatible with Hadoop Distributed File System.
SupportsOrdering
The Partitioner implementing this feature indicates it is ordering-aware that workflow engine shall assure the same sorting order of all partitions of output DataFrame must be preserved in the downstream localization process.
SupportsPartitioning
The loader operator implementing this feature indicates it is partition-aware that workflow engine shall assure the same data partition across multiple input data sources must be in the same Spark executor in localization process.
SupportsReadingDataFrame
The loader operator implementing this feature indicates it supports loading input files and returns Spark DataFrame.
SupportsReadingDeltaTable
The loader operator implementing this feature indicates it supports loading delta table and returns Spark DataFrame.
SupportsRepartitioning
The collector operator implementing this feature supports repartitioning the content of output files from shell command execution.
SupportsSaveToBLOB
The writer operator implementing this feature supports saving output dataframe in object storage; for instance, using df.write.format("parquet").option("key", "value").save(path).
SupportsSaveToHTTP
The writer operator implementing this feature supports putting the content of the DataFrame to a remote HTTP/HTTPS repository.
SupportsSaveToJDBC
The writer operator implementing this feature supports saving the content of the DataFrame to an external database table via JDBC.
SupportsTableLocalization
The executor operator implementing this feature supports returning a DataFrame table for SQL command execution.
SupportsUDF1<T1,R>
The formatter operator implementing this feature supports user-defined function that has 1 arguments, i.e.
SupportsUDF2<T1,T2,R>
The formatter operator implementing this feature supports user-defined function that has 2 arguments, i.e.
SupportsUDF3<T1,T2,T3,R>
The formatter operator implementing this feature supports user-defined function that has 3 arguments, i.e.
SupportsUDF4<T1,T2,T3,T4,R>
The formatter operator implementing this feature supports user-defined function that has 4 arguments, i.e.
SupportsUDF5<T1,T2,T3,T4,T5,R>
The formatter operator implementing this feature supports user-defined function that has 5 arguments, i.e.
Writer
An operator object responsible for delocalizing/saving output DataFrame to storage or repositories, e.g.
WriterSupport
Factory object responsible for creating Writer operators.
